I am always on the hunt for catastrophic ordering algorithms

thus I present the Bradley-Terry model, fit to the LumiRank 2023 database

requirements are that players need (about) 20+ sets

(NOTE: THIS ORDERING IS NOT AFFILIATED WITH LUMIRANK) https://t.co/u8XlX4uXcW
Also, honorable mentions: the players that would have been top 500 if they met the 20 set minimum! https://t.co/oUvU2UNSZN

The Bradley-Terry model is basically built on a function that estimates the probability of a set being won or lost. It then assigns scores to every player to maximize the probability of the actual results happening

As such, it's really sensitive to huge upsets and values consistency a LOT, and is almost completely ignorant of attendance (beating lots of people is still good though)
